<Class name="Spooler" id="e8e54a3e-a024-46df-ad19-9c2cb45f5924">
    <superclass name="Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>PURPOSE:
========

Automatic handling of FTP files.

Two distinct parts:

1. SpoolerServer
----------------

	SpoolerServer app must reside on the FTP Server.
	
	Handles Inwards FTP files by executing spoolAFile method() (user-reimplemented).
	Handles standing Jobs containing Batches of files to be sent Outwards.
	Handles one-time GUI FTP jobs entered via FTP Job Definition and Maintenance 
	(FtpJobMaint form).
	
2. FtpCopyServer
----------------

	Handles copying files to and from App directories to the FTP server directories.
	(copyToApp() and copyFromApp()).
	
	A timerEvent() check a queue of FtpCopyQ objects for work, and also scans
	specified directories to create FtpCopyQ objects for the queue. 
	
		If the FtpCopyServer is residing on the FTP server then it will process
		FtpCopyQ objects to copy files from the App to FTP directories. It will also
		check Inwards FTP directories for files to be copied to the App.
		
		If the FtpCopyServer is not resident on the FTP server then it will create
		FtpCopyQ objects to be processed by the FTP Server-resident FtpCopyServer to 
		copy files from the App directories to FTP directories.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="FtpData"/>
</Class>
